M|Plan|tx|Use this template when dispatching a plan document reviewer subagent.
M|Plan|**Pu|** Verify the plan is complete, matches the spec, and has proper task decomposition.
M|Plan|**Di|** The complete plan is written.
M|Plan|tx|```
M|Plan|Task|
M|Plan|desc|"rv plan document"
M|Plan|pm|\|
M|Plan|tx|You are a plan document reviewer. Verify this plan is complete and ready for implementation.
M|Plan|**Pl|** [PLAN_FILE_PATH]
M|Plan|**Sp|** [SPEC_FILE_PATH]
M|What|tx|\| Category \| What to Look For \|
M|What|tx|\|----------\|------------------\|
M|What|tx|\| Completeness \| TODOs, placeholders, incomplete tasks, missing steps \|
M|What|tx|\| Spec Alignment \| Plan covers spec requirements, no major scope creep \|
M|What|tx|\| Task Decomposition \| Tasks have clear boundaries, steps are actionable \|
M|What|tx|\| Buildability \| cld an engineer follow this plan w/o getting stuck? \|
M|Cali|tx|**Only flag issues that wld cause real problems during implementation.**
M|Cali|tx|An implementer building the wrong thing or getting stuck is an issue.
M|Cali|tx|Minor wording, stylistic preferences, and "nice to have" suggestions are not.
M|Cali|tx|ap unless there are serious gaps — missing requirements from the spec,
M|Cali|tx|contradictory steps, placeholder cn, or tasks so vague they can't be acted on.
M|Plan|**St|** Approved \| Issues Found
M|Plan|**Is|**
M|Plan|- [T|[specific issue] - [why it matters for implementation]
M|Plan|**Re|**
M|Plan|it|[suggestions for improvement]
M|Plan|tx|```
